TITLE: Calling EntityCollectionService commands in Angular Component with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines component methods that invoke command functions on the EntityCollectionService instance. These commands include getAll() to fetch all entities, add() to add a new entity, delete() to remove an entity by id, and update() to update an existing entity object. Each command dispatches NgRx data actions to either query or modify the cached entity collection and sync with the server asynchronously.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ngrx/platform/blob/main/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/data/entity-collection-service.md#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
getHeroes() { this.heroService.getAll(); }
