TITLE: Managing Paginator State Using ComponentStore in a Service - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Defines a PaginatorStore service that extends Angular's ComponentStore to encapsulate the paginator component's business logic. It uses updaters to handle state mutation triggered by incoming @Input values or user interactions, and effects to derive additional state or handle side effects. The store exposes selectors including a combined ViewModel observable (vm$) for template consumption and a debounced page$ observable emitting PageEvents on state change. Dependencies include Angular ComponentStore and relevant Angular Material paginator types. Inputs like pageIndex and pageSize are passed to updaters to update the internal state; outputs reflect derived states and event notifications.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ngrx/platform/blob/main/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/component-store/usage.md#_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
/* Example snippet showing input updaters in PaginatorStore */
readonly setPageIndex = this.updater<number>((state, pageIndex) => ({ ...state, pageIndex }));
readonly setPageSize = this.updater<number>((state, pageSize) => ({ ...state, pageSize }));

/* Effect for handling page change emitted on state update, debounced to avoid intermediary emissions */
readonly page$ = this.select(
  this.state$,
  state => ({ pageIndex: state.pageIndex, pageSize: state.pageSize }),
  { debounce: true }
);

/* Exposing a ViewModel observable aggregating multiple selectors for template binding */
readonly vm$ = this.select(
  this.select(state => state.pageIndex),
  this.select(state => state.pageSize),
  (pageIndex, pageSize) => ({ pageIndex, pageSize })
);
```

