TITLE: Manual Cleanup for signalMethod by Providing Injector in Angular TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates providing the local component injector as an option when invoking a signalMethod created in an ancestor injection context. This manual cleanup ensures that the effect is tied to the component lifecycle, preventing memory leaks. Static value inputs do not require injector provision. This pattern depends on Angular's dependency injection and signal handling.
