TITLE: Defining Custom Ngrx Router Navigation Actions
DESCRIPTION: Provides the TypeScript definitions for custom Ngrx actions that represent router navigation events. These actions (`GO`, `BACK`, `FORWARD`) replace the deprecated built-in ones and are designed to be dispatched from components or services.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ngrx/platform/blob/main/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/migration/v4.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { Action } from '@ngrx/store';
import { NavigationExtras } from '@angular/router';

export const GO = '[Router] Go';
export const BACK = '[Router] Back';
export const FORWARD = '[Router] Forward';

export class Go implements Action {
  readonly type = GO;

  constructor(
    public payload: {
      path: any[];
      query?: object;
      extras?: NavigationExtras;
    }
  ) {}
}

export class Back implements Action {
  readonly type = BACK;
}

export class Forward implements Action {
  readonly type = FORWARD;
}

export type Actions = Go | Back | Forward;
```

