TITLE: Correct Effect implementation with OnRunEffects interface - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example illustrates the correct implementation of the `OnRunEffects` interface. The class `Effect` now implements the `OnRunEffects` interface, and the `ngrxOnRunEffects` method is appropriately defined within the class, preventing the linting error. Import statement is included.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ngrx/platform/blob/main/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/eslint-plugin/rules/use-effects-lifecycle-interface.md#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { OnRunEffects } from '@ngrx/effects';

class Effect implements OnRunEffects {
  constructor(private actions$: Actions) {}
  ngrxOnRunEffects(resolvedEffects$: Observable<EffectNotification>) {
    return this.actions$.pipe(
      ofType('LOGGED_IN'),
      exhaustMap(() =>
        resolvedEffects$.pipe(
          takeUntil(this.actions$.pipe(ofType('LOGGED_OUT')))
        )
      )
    );
  }
}
```

