TITLE: Testing Functional NgRx Effects with Fake Dependencies - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This test verifies a functional NgRx effect by passing in mock arguments for actions and services, eliminating the need for Angular's TestBed. It constructs an observable actions stream and supplies a mock ActorsService with a getAll method returning a value. The test confirms that the effect emits a success action with the correct payload. Dependencies include RxJS 'of', the loadActors effect function, and mock service/action creators. Key parameters are the input stream and service; expected output is a success action observable. The pattern enables isolated function-level testing.
