DESCRIPTION: Provides an Angular component example demonstrating the behavior of `*ngrxLet` before v15 when handling observable replacement leading to a suspense state. When the button is clicked and `obs$` is replaced with a delayed observable, the existing view (`<p>`) is not immediately removed; instead, the template variable `o` becomes `undefined` until the new observable emits.
