TITLE: Manual Cleanup of Dispatched EffectRef in Angular Component (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to manually destroy an EffectRef returned by NgRx store.dispatch, ensuring proper resource cleanup. The BookComponent creates the effect in ngOnInit by dispatching a signal-derived action, then destroys it in ngOnDestroy to prevent memory leaks. Dependencies: EffectRef type (from NgRx or Angular CDK), injected Store. Inputs: signal (bookId); Output: effect teardown.
SOURCE: https://github.com/ngrx/platform/blob/main/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/store/actions.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
class BookComponent {
  bookId = input.required<number>();
  loadBookEffectRef: EffectRef | undefined;
  store = inject(Store);

  ngOnInit() {
    // uses the injection context of Store, i.e. root injector
    this.loadBookEffectRef = this.store.dispatch(() => loadBook({ id: this.bookId() }));
  }

  ngOnDestroy() {
    if (this.loadBookEffectRef) {
      // destroys the effect
      this.loadBookEffectRef.destroy();
    }
  }
}
```

